pageContext.claim: “And our country is doing very well.  Economically, we've never had anything like it.”
pageContext.analysis: The annual increase in the gross domestic product, the broadest measure of the economy, is currently far below the level reached in many years in the 1930s, 1940s, 1950s, 1960s, 1970s, 1980s, 1990s and 2000s.
